I"R.<p>I was given orders just today that I ‘need to update my blog so certain people can keep track of my shenanigans.’ So here it is, the latest instalment of Happy Seizure, an account of the hijinks and  insight into the mind of yours truly.</p>

<p>Since leaving Whistler, the plan of attack was to hit up Nanaimo, since I’d never been there and all the research I did told me it was a pretty bangin’ little town. They had one thing right: little. As for bangin’, well if you’re into industrial towns then yeh, but otherwise it was pretty bland. It never helps to be in a small town when it’s either rainy or a weekend, and as my luck had it, both. It would be a cool little base to drive to other parts of the island or if you wanted to bungy/zipline/etc, though I didn’t have a car and I’d prefer to do some of those activites in much more scenic places.</p>

<p>As such, I only took one photo in Nanaimo. It’s of the bay where the seaplanes were moored.</p>

